Generic single-database configuration for RedSentinel.

## Usage

### Create a new migration
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Downgrade migrations
```bash
alembic downgrade -1  # Downgrade one version
alembic downgrade base  # Downgrade to initial state
```

### View migration history
```bash
alembic history
alembic current
```

### Merge multiple heads
```bash
alembic merge heads -m "merge message"
```

## Notes

- Migrations are automatically detected based on model changes
- Always review generated migrations before applying
- Test migrations in development before production
- Keep migrations in version control

